{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"illadvised-sophomoric-jellyfish","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nThe single source of truth for every metric the command surfaces: a declarative registry mapping each metric id to its lens, data source, and compute, plus the graceful `unavailable{reason,accruing_since}` state and the `source`+`confidence` labels — so the command is written once and never modified as new signals accrue, and a classified/backfilled value is never aggregated into an authoritative structural series.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/__init__.py` — new package.\n- `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` — new: `MetricSpec` (id, lens, source, confidence, compute), the `REGISTRY`, `MetricValue`/`Unavailable` result types, and an `is_authoritative(source)` segregation helper.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_registry.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nA declarative registry (not per-metric scattered code) is what makes the command complete-once: rendering iterates the registry, and a metric with no data yet returns `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` rather than being absent, so a new signal lights up by populating its source with no CLI change. `source` in {structural, git, sidecar, snapshot, backfill_classified} and `confidence` in {high, classified} ride on every value so downstream aggregation can keep high-confidence structural series apart from fuzzy backfills. Additive and standalone — no existing behavior changes.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (in-process, real registry): a metric whose compute returns no data yields `Unavailable` with populated `reason` + `accruing_since`; `is_authoritative('backfill_classified')` is False and a classified value is excluded from an authoritative rollup helper.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_registry.py` passes: every `REGISTRY` entry has a unique id, a `lens`, a `source`, and a `confidence` — asserted by collecting the registry and checking `len(ids) == len(set(ids))`.\n- [ ] A metric with no data returns `Unavailable` carrying a non-empty `reason` and an ISO `accruing_since` — unit test asserts both fields present.\n- [ ] `is_authoritative('backfill_classified')` is False and an authoritative aggregation excludes classified values — unit test asserts a mixed input yields a series containing only `source in {structural,git,sidecar,snapshot}`.","id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Metric registry + unavailable-state & source/confidence label contract"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416577550676001,"uuid":"d170116c-8e7e-4be4-8915-8c6c99518923"}